  shortDescription: A pair of old ice climbing picks, mounted on the wall. Scuffed
    and well-used. K2, 1998.
  fullStory: "1998 \u2014 The K2 expedition. There was a storm. Three men on the
    rope. One came home."
  marthaContext: "Robert was brave. The storm was impossible. He tried to hold the
    rope \u2014 he fought as hard as any man could. He couldn\u2019t save them. David
    was on the radio at basecamp. It was a tragedy. Not Robert\u2019s fault."
  davidContext: "David was at basecamp on the radio during the K2 storm. He heard
    Arthur screaming before the line went quiet. Then Robert cut his comms. David
    has never said this to Robert\u2019s face. Not until now."
